SIMPLE: fagot
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fagot
<hw>fag"ot</hw> <pr>(f⟦acr⟧g"⟦ucr⟧t)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., prob.
aug. of L. <ets>fax</ets>, <ets>facis</ets>, torch, perh. orig., a
bundle of sticks; cf. Gr. <grk>fa`kelos</grk> bundle, fagot. Cf.
<er>Fagotto</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A bundle of sticks, twigs, or
small branches of trees, used for fuel, for raising batteries, filling
ditches, or other purposes in fortification; a fascine.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bundle of pieces of wrought iron to be worked over
into bars or other shapes by rolling or hammering at a welding heat; a
pile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A bassoon. See
<er>Fagotto</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A person hired to take the place of another at the
muster of a company.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>An old shriveled woman.</def> <mark>[Slang,
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fagot iron</b></col>, <cd>iron, in bars or masses,
manufactured from fagots.</cd> -- <col><b>Fagot vote</b></col>, <cd>the
vote of a person who has been constituted a voter by being made a
landholder, for party purposes.</cd> <mark>[Political cant,
Eng.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fagot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fagot
<hw>Fag"ot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Fagoted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Fagoting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To make a fagot of; to bind
together in a fagot or bundle; also, to collect promiscuously.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fagotto</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
